<center><h3><font color="blue">Chapter 11</font></h3>
<h1>Presentation Rate and Resolution </h1>
</center>
<hr size=3>

<h3>

<img src="blue.gif"> <i>Problem</i> :  Network has restricted capacity and limited buffering<p>
<img src="blue.gif"> <i>Solution</i> : Prefetching , deliver object partially<p>
<img src="blue.gif"> User can specify the following parameters <p>
<ol>
<li><i> Maximum allowable percentage data loss</i> : acceptable data loss for each object 
<li><i> Presentation rate ratio</i> : ratio of the required rate of presentation to the nominal one 
</ol>
<img src="blue.gif"><i> Example</i>  : every third frame can be dropped in NTSC quality video

<p>
The following table shows reliability of multimedia information type <p>
<center>
<table cellpadding=10 border=5>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 align=center> <b>Reliability</b>
<td align=center><b> Voice </b>
<td align=center><b> Video </b>
<td align=center><b> Image </b>
<td align=center><b> Text </b>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align=center> 0.98 
<td align=center> 0.90
<td align=center> 1.0
<td align=center> 1.0
</tr>
